Your Beauty lies in Plain Sight. Plain, simple and the girl next door. People tend overlook you as you are the
"normal girl", but you're actually very beautiful. And you have plenty about you to
set you apart, but more that lets you blend. People love the stability you have
because as others may come and go, you will always be there and you may always
be the same. You like simple things and that's what people like about you. You
most likely enjoy things most consider normal, like movies, shopping, that sort
of thing and are very friendly and probably have many friends. You are sweet and
kind and that shows on you, but you're also strong and not very naive. You're a
rather well-rounded individual. Even though some people pass you off as
just another girl, shrug it off because they don't know what they're
missing.

One of my favourite KISS members died of Cancer 13 years ago on the 24th November 1991. That person was Eric Carr. I figured since he was one of the best drummers in the world and a inspiration to everyone everywhere he deserves a memorial post from me. He was a drummer who replaced Peter Criss in 1980 when they changed line-up's after Peter "left" because of "artistic differences"(druggie problem).

I'm not going to brag on about someone most of you probably dont know about but he got onto the walk of fame with the rest of the KISS members and after 11 years of being with the band ... he has left a legacy of fans and some really great drumming on some kiss tunes.

<center>God Bless You Eric!!!</center>

Last nite was the last episode of the NRL Footy Show (Note: NRL not the "other" AFL where they hop around the stadium like ballerina's LMFAO) for 2004. I'm gonna miss Matty Johns and his Reg Reagan character .. too funny. I should buy the dvd soon. :) Can't believe it's October.. this means it's not long till Christmas and pressie time. ;p

That's my post i guess for today ...
http://cool-kisschick.livejournal.com/2913.html

Anyway onto the fun stuff ...

We saw all these exhibits of Australian wildlife under water. From the platypus to the things that you all probably saw in "Finding Nemo" and yes I FOUND NEMO !!!! We went around all the place and saw some really neat stuff like what kind of fish live on the Great Barrier Reef and where some of the sharks are.. I did see some sharks and it was cool... 

After finishing looking around the Aquarium.. we went on the monorail which does a loop around darling harbour and the city twice and got off where all the cafe's are in darling harbour and went and had cafe there. EXPENSIVE!! costed me nearly $15 just for 2 latte's and a piece of chocolate mud cake (mmmmm! mud cake *homer drool sound*)

After that .. I decided I was too tired and we went home. So all in all we had a good day. Now I have to go and do stuff .. I'd rather stay home and veg out but I CAN'T!!!

Later All :)
http://cool-kisschick.livejournal.com/2689.html

Yesterday (Monday October 4th) was Labour Day in NSW. So what better way to celebrate the fact that it was a long weekend but go out for the day... Andy and I went to the Sydney Aquarium (I'd post the pics we took but they came out too blurred on the digital camera) For those who wanna check what the place looks like, check out the web addy at the bottom of the post.

So we caught the ferry to Darling Harbour which is a cool place to go visit .. a lot of shops and attractions there and on the way there on the ferry we went past the Opera House, Luna Park and went under the Sydney Harbour Bridge which is really cool. When we got there, we had lunch at the restaurant at the Aquarium and the calamari was yum! ;p 

After lunch (because it was a last minute decision to go out cuz we were bored @ home LOL) we went into the Aquarium and saw all of the attractions there. I must say that all of the attractions were really cool ... but what stood out the most I'll post again :) cuz it's a long one


Web Addys:
==========

* Sydney Aquarium - http://www.sydneyaquarium.com.au
* Luna Park (Sydney) - http://www.lunaparksydney.com.au
* Darling Harbour - http://www.darlingharbour.com/index.cfm

It's been a LONG while but I think it's time I updated you all who read of my life on what I have been doing and when things have taken place... Right now it is RAINING for the 4th day in a row and it's annoying me because it's too cold. Went out to eastie's today and I froze my butt off. Anyway on with it:

April:
- Andy's drum workshop at the Spastic Center of NSW went well... 30 people turned up and had a great time.

May:
- KISS CONCERT 18th May 2004: I was upfront of the stage in the moshpit and oh my god the show rocked!!! No matter what the critics say.. I still think they kick ass even though they may have sold out.. The supporting acts were a little crappy .. Machine Gun Fellatio sucked! Can't sing, do theatrical or get their stuff together onstage. Grinspoon followed after them and they were half decent.

- My birthday 22nd May 2004: I am now 24 years old! Predictably I got some clothes for my birthday, cd's and some stuff.. can't remember what .. but what really made my b'day special is the saki bottle/cup and the fan my brother brought from Tokyo, Japan a few months ago (June 2004) That made me so happy!!!

- Drummer's Festival 29-30th May 2004: Had a great time there... stayed at the Ibis hotel @ Olympic Park and the actual festival was at the Telstra Stadium. Saw and met some really cool drummers. A good friend of Andy's and mine was a guest performer and it was really cool to see him do his stuff.

June:
Being winter ... cant remember what I did

July:
My best friend's birthday was in July :o)

August:
- Club Wild @ The Opera House (http://www.clubwild.net/opera%20house.html) 7th August 2004: Andy was lucky enough to play at the opera house with club wild. It was sooooooo cool to actually have backstage passes and everything. Go to his website (addy at the top) and have a look at the review there. Oh and by the way .. a VERY BIG shout to our friends at Drum City Sydney (http://www.drumcity.com.au) and Billy Hyde Drumcraft (http://www.drumcraft.com.au) for all their support on the day.

- Billy Hyde Playoffs 21st August 2004: Andy played a 30 minute guest presentation set at the playoffs in hoping that the kids would be inspired by Andy's drumming and what he's achieved despite his CP (Cerebral Palsy). The info for that is on his website.

September:
Can't remember

And that's it till now.. 

Rock and Roll All NITE!!!
